
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconColor Blue

class Doctor {
  +String practitionerNumber
  +String fullName
  +String address
  +String phoneNumber
  +Image digitalSignature
  +Date validityDate
  +List<Test> prescribedTests
  +String repetitionCount
  +RepetitionInterval repetitionInterval
}

class Patient {
  +String healthNumber
  +String firstName
  +String lastName
  +Date dateOfBirth
  +String address
  +String phoneNumber
  +List<Requisition> requisitions
  +List<Appointment> appointments
}

class Requisition {
  +String id
  +Doctor doctor
  +Patient patient
  +List<Test> tests
  +Date validityDate
  +Integer repetitionCount
  +RepetitionInterval repetitionInterval
}

class Test {
  +String name
  +String testGroup
  +Duration duration
  +Boolean requiresAppointment
  +Boolean isWalkInOnly
  +Boolean requiresSampleDropOff
}

class Appointment {
  +String confirmationNumber
  +Date appointmentDate
  +Time startTime
  +Time endTime
  +Lab lab
  +Requisition requisition
  +Double fee
}

class Lab {
  +String name
  +String address
  +String registrationNumber
  +Time businessStartHour
  +Time businessEndHour
  +List<Test> availableTests
  +Double cancellationFee
}

enum RepetitionInterval {
  WEEKLY, MONTHLY, EVERY_HALF_YEAR, YEARLY
}

Doctor "1" -- "0..*" Requisition : prescribes
Patient "1" -- "0..*" Requisition : submits
Requisition "1" -- "1" Doctor : belongsTo
Requisition "1" -- "1" Patient : belongsTo
Requisition "1" -- "1.." Test : includes
Test "1" -- "0..*" Requisition : partOf
Requisition "1" -- "0..1" Appointment : has
Appointment "1" -- "1" Lab : at
Appointment "1" -- "1" Requisition : for
Lab "1" -- "0..*" Test : offers
Test "1" -- "0..*" Lab : offeredAt
@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Classes and Relationships:

- **Doctor**: Has personal info, signature, and can prescribe tests to patients (but not themselves).
- **Patient**: Has personal info and manages their own requisitions and appointments.
- **Requisition**: Contains tests from the same group, patient and doctor info, and repetition rules.
- **Test**: Defined by lab, with attributes like duration, whether it needs an appointment, or sample drop-off.
- **Appointment**: A scheduled time for a test, tied to a specific lab and requisition. Includes fees and cancellation policy.
- **Lab**: Manages its own schedule, available tests, and fees.

- **Enums**: `RepetitionInterval` defines how often tests are repeated.

